E. COLI, PREVENTION OF HUS, CLINICAL TRIAL - USA
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
E. coli, toxigenic, county fair - USA (New York) 990906105130
Date: Tue, 7 Sep 1999 11:48:04 -0600
From: Bernadette van der Boom bboom@synsorb.com>

We have an investigational product with which we are conducting [phase III
clinical trials to determine it's effectiveness for the Prevention of
Hemolytic Uremic Syndrome (HUS) in children with proven _E. coli_ infections.
We have a site at the Montefiore Center in New York. The principal
investigator at this site is Dr. Catherine Sellinger. Those who would like
to participate in this study may contact her at 718-920-5312.
There is also an NIH funded study being coordinated by Dr. Howard Trachtman
for the Treatment of Hemolytic Uremic Syndrome. Those who would like to
participate in this study may contact her at 718-470-3491.
--
